---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Scrabble Words With Double R — CORRIDOR, TERRIFIC, BARRIER & More"
  description="Best double-R words for Scrabble. CORRIDOR (11pts), TERRIFIC (13pts), BARRIER (9pts). RR pattern strategy for mid-game scoring. Free word finder."
  keywords="scrabble double r words, corridor scrabble, terrific scrabble, barrier scrabble, rr words scrabble, double r strategy, double letter words"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Scrabble Words With Double R — CORRIDOR, TERRIFIC, BARRIER & More",
    "description": "Best double-R Scrabble words. RR pattern strategy for mid-game scoring.",
    "datePublished": "2026-06-30",
    "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com" },
    "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" },
    "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-words-with-double-r" }
  })} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "What are the highest scoring double-R words?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "TERRIFIC (13pts), CORRIDOR (11pts), and BARRIER (9pts). All are bingo-eligible at 7-8 letters." } },
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "How many R tiles are in a Scrabble bag?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "There are 6 R tiles worth 1 point each, making RR draws fairly common." } },
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "What short RR words are valid?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "ERR (3pts) is the shortest. PURR (6pts), BURR (6pts), PARR (6pts) are strong 4-letter options." } }
    ]
  })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a><span class="mx-1">›</span><span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words With Double R — CORRIDOR, TERRIFIC, BARRIER & More</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><span>4 min read</span><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">Six R tiles in the bag means RR pairs show up regularly. Double-R words tend to be longer, familiar words — perfect for bingos and mid-game plays that keep your score climbing steadily.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">13 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">TERRIFIC</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">11 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">CORRIDOR</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">9 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">BARRIER</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">6</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">R tiles in bag</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top Double-R Words</h2>

      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 Top RR Word</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">TERRIFIC — 13 Points</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">T=1, E=1, R=1, R=1, I=1, F=4, I=1, C=3 · 8 letters</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">F and C provide scoring punch while RR sits in the middle. With the bingo bonus, TERRIFIC scores 63 total points.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🏢 CORRIDOR</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">11 pts · 8 letters · D=2 + RR core</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🚧 BARRIER</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">9 pts · 7 letters · B=3 + RR · Bingo</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🔮 MIRROR</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">8 pts · 6 letters · M=3 + double-R</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🐦 SPARROW</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">12 pts · 7 letters · W=4, P=3 + RR</p></div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">RR Pattern Strategy</h2>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">RR in the middle:</span> Most RR words place doubles mid-word — BARRIER, CARROT, MIRROR. Look for consonant-RR-vowel patterns on your rack.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">ERR as a hook base:</span> ERR hooks into ERROR, ERRAND, ERRATIC. Play it early to create extension opportunities for later turns.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">PURR/BURR for tight spots:</span> These 4-letter words score 6 points and fit cramped positions where longer RR words won't reach.</p></div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">CORRECT</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">11pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">NARRATE</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">7pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">CARROT</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">8pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">WARRANT</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">10pts</span></span>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Pattern Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">RR words average <span class="text-white font-medium">6.8 letters</span>. Adding -ED, -ING, or -ER often pushes them to 7+ for the bingo bonus.</p>
      </div>

      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-with-double-l/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words With Double L</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-with-double-s/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words With Double S</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find double-R words from your rack — free Scrabble solver, instant results</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center"><a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a></div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
